{"title_page": "Explained (TV series)", "text_new": "{{Italic title}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Explained\n| image                    = Explained Logo.jpg\n| genre                    = Documentary\n| creator                  = {{Unbulleted list|[[Ezra Klein]]|Joe Posner}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Jackson Greenberg\n| num_seasons              = 2<!--Only increment as the series premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| num_episodes             = 35<!--Only increment as a new episode premieres, per the documentation of the template!-->\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{Unbulleted list|Ezra Klein|Kara Rozansky|Claire Gordon|Chad Mumm|Lisa Nishimura|Joe Posner|Jason Spingarn-Koff|Kate Townsend}}\n| cinematography           = {{Plain list |\n* Cory Popp\n* Doug Camberis\n* Mario Furloni\n* Andrew Berends\n}}\n| runtime                  = 14\u201326 minutes\n| company                  = [[Vox (website)|Vox]]\n| distributor              = [[Netflix]]\n| network                  = Netflix\n| website                  = https://www.netflix.com/title/80216752\n| website_title            = Official website\n| released                 = {{Start date|2018|5|23}}\n| related                  = {{ubl|''[[The Mind, Explained]]''|''[[Sex, Explained]]''}}\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n}}\n'''''Explained''''' is an American [[Television documentary|documentary television series]] that premiered on [[Netflix]] on May 23, 2018. The show, which is produced by [[Vox Media]], releases episodes on a weekly basis.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.vox.com/2018/5/23/17378322/vox-netflix-show-explained|title=Vox's Netflix show \"Explained,\" explained|work=Vox|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref> ''Explained'' is based on Vox's previous [[YouTube]] videos series, which followed a similar format.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.niemanlab.org/2018/05/voxs-new-netflix-series-is-really-good-but-it-doesnt-get-us-any-closer-to-figuring-out-what-news-on-streaming-platforms-looks-like/|title=Vox's new Netflix series is really good, but it doesn't get us any closer to figuring out what news on streaming platforms looks like|work=Nieman Lab|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref>\n\nThe show's episodes average between 16\u201318 minutes, with each focusing on a different topic.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.indiewire.com/2018/05/explained-netflix-review-vox-documentary-show-1201967788/|title='Explained' Review: Netflix's Intriguing Docuseries Tackles Every Topic in the World, From K-Pop to DNA, in 20 Minute Chunks|last=Greene|first=Steve|date=2018-05-24|work=IndieWire|access-date=2018-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref> Each episode is also voiced by a different guest narrator.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.whats-on-netflix.com/news/every-narrator-on-voxs-netflix-series-explained/|title=Every Narrator on Vox's Netflix Series \"Explained\" - What's on Netflix|date=2018-08-22|work=What's on Netflix|access-date=2018-08-29|language=en-US}}</ref> Netflix ordered 20 episodes for the show's first season,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.recode.net/2018/5/24/17386554/vox-netflix-explained-ezra-klein-explainer-video-youtube-peter-kafka-media-podcast|title=Why Vox's Netflix show 'Explained' is different from Vox's YouTube videos, explained (by Ezra Klein)|work=Recode|access-date=2018-08-28}}</ref> and greenlit a second season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/explained-netflix-vox-media-season-2-1202501589/|title=Netflix Docuseries 'Explained' Greenlit For Season 2|work=Deadline|access-date=2018-11-16}}</ref> The second season debuted on September 26, 2019.\n\nThe show has also spawned three [[Spin-off (media)|spin-off]] limited series. On September 12, 2019, ''[[The Mind, Explained]]'' was released on Netflix. The 5-episode series focused specifically on topics related to the human brain. On January 4, 2020, a follow-up titled ''[[Sex, Explained]]'' was released, with episodes centered around the theme of sex.<ref name=\"TDB20\">{{cite news |last1=Julian |first1=Jordan |title=Janelle Mon\u00e1e Explains Your Sexual Fantasies in Netflix\u2019s Sex-Ed Docuseries |url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/sex-explained-review-janelle-monae-explains-your-sexual-fantasies-and-more |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=The Daily Beast |date=4 January 2020 |ref=TDB20}}</ref> On April 25, 2020, ''[[Coronavirus, Explained]]'' will be released. The 3-episode series will focus on the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Jarvey |first1=Natalie |title=Netflix Unpacks Coronavirus Pandemic With New Season of 'Explained' |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/netflix-unpacks-coronavirus-pandemic-new-season-explained-1291877 |website=hollywoodreporter.com |publisher=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=April 25, 2020 |date=April 25, 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n== Episodes ==\n===Season 1 (2018)===\n{{Episode table |total_width=70 |background=#fff800 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=30 |Aux1=35 |aux1T=Narrator |airdate=30 |airdateR=<ref name=\"TFC\">{{cite web |title= Explained \u2013 Listings |url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/explained/listings/ |website=[[The Futon Critic]] |accessdate=August 30, 2019}}</ref> |released=y |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 1\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 1\n|Title           = The Racial Wealth Gap\n|Aux1            = [[Samira Wiley]]\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|23}}\n|ShortSummary    = A look at the [[Economic inequality|wealth gap]] among races in the US and its causes, including [[Slavery in the United States|slavery]] and [[racial segregation]]. Featuring Senator [[Cory Booker]], [[Mehrsa Baradaran]], and [[Thomas Shapiro]].\n|LineColor       = fff800\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 2\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 2\n|Title           = Designer DNA\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|5|23}}\n|Aux1            = Joss Fong\n|ShortSummary    = Scientists and experts discuss the ri