out the science and history behind the [[Orgasm#Females|female orgasm]], and ways modern women approach the subject. Featuring [[Lisa M. Diamond]], [[Mireille Miller-Young]], [[Beverly Whipple]], and [[Paula England]].\n|LineColor       = fff800\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 17\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 17\n|Title           = Political Correctness\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|8|29}}\n|Aux1            = [[Jerry Springer]]\n|ShortSummary    = A look at the debate surrounding [[political correctness]], including talks of [[free speech]], [[hate speech]], and [[Inclusivism|inclusivity]], and how \"PC-culture\" has influenced politics. Featuring [[W. Kamau Bell]], [[Julia Serano]], [[Glenn Beck]], and [[John L. Jackson Jr.]].\n|LineColor       = fff800\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 18\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 18\n|Title           = Why Women Are Paid Less\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|9|5}}\n|Aux1            = [[Rachel McAdams]]\n|ShortSummary    = Discussions on the [[gender pay gap]] and the [[Women in the workforce|rights of women in the workplace]]. Featuring [[Valentine Rugwabiza]], [[Hillary Clinton]], [[Greta Van Susteren]], [[Katr\u00edn Jakobsd\u00f3ttir]], and [[Anne-Marie Slaughter]].\n|LineColor       = fff800\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 19\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 19\n|Title           = The World's Water Crisis\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|9|12}}\n|Aux1            = [[Kyle MacLachlan]]\n|ShortSummary    = An examination of the [[Water scarcity|water crisis]] around the world, including ideas on how to protect [[Drinking water|clean water]] and ensuring third-world countries continue to have access. Featuring [[Amina Mohamed]].\n|LineColor       = fff800\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber   = 20\n|EpisodeNumber2  = 20\n|Title           = Music\n|OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2018|9|19}}\n|Aux1            = [[Carly Rae Jepsen]]\n|ShortSummary    = A brief [[history of music]], and a discussion on the definitions of [